HEADWORD: Paramours
<hw>Par"a*mours`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <def>By or with love, esp. the love of the sexes; --
sometimes written as two words.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For <qex>par amour</qex>, I loved her first ere thou.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paramylum</ent>⟦br⟧
